cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel architectural enhancement of deep convolutional neural network (CNN) for learning discriminative patterns. It also utilizes Transfer Learning (TL) which is a popular technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as CNNs are widely used in AI applications such as image and speech recognition. 

The paper also involves image processing and feature extraction, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Furthermore, the use of TL and the focus on improving the representative capacity of the network suggests it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves churn prediction in telecom, which could suggest it belongs to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
